<h1>Montgomery Calgary Real Estate and Homes for Sale</h1>
<p>Montgomery is a family-friendly community with oodles of small-town charm and a warm and safe atmosphere. The picturesque Bow River, Shouldice Park and Edworthy Park add to Montgomery's vivid natural beauty. A vibrant shopping community and active community association round out Montgomery's many appealing features.</p>

<div>#idx-c-montgomery#</div>

<div class="community-writeup">
    <div style="margin-top: 80px;">
        <div style="background: linear-gradient(100deg, rgba(0,0,0,0.8) 0%, rgba(0,0,0,0.8) 100%), url('https://www.calgary-real-estate.com/uploads/agent-1/community/nw-calgary/montgomery/amenities/montgomery-wm-56.webp'); background-size: cover; min-height: 300px; background-position: center; display: flex; align-items: center; padding: 10%; border-radius: 3px; box-shadow: rgba(50, 50, 93, 0.25) 0px 13px 27px -5px, rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.3) 0px 8px 16px -8px; margin-bottom: 30px;">
            <h2 style="color: #f9f9f9; margin-bottom: 0; padding-bottom: 0; font-size: 35px; line-height: 1.2; text-shadow: 0px 0px 2px #FFFFFF;">
                Montgomery Real Estate &mdash; <span style="text-transform: initial;">a family-friendly, inner-city NW Calgary neighbourhood.</span>
            </h2>
        </div>
        <div class="grid_12">
            <div class="x6">
                <p>Montgomery is a residential community located in North West Calgary, bordered on the East by Shaganappi Trail and on the North by 32nd Avenue and Market Mall. The family-friendly, inner-city neighbourhood is located just minutes away from downtown Calgary on the banks of the tranquil Bow River. The community of <a href="https://www.real-estate.ca/bowness.php">Bowness</a> lies just across the river to the West of Montgomery. The neighbourhood is distinguished by expansive outdoor spaces, cycling paths, kidsâ€™ playgrounds and picnic areas.</p>
                <p>Shouldice Park, a notable landmark in Montgomery, is a whopping 28 hectares of outdoor space that includes picnic grounds, soccer fields, and batting cages-all located within easy access to Bow River. Another beautiful outdoor space in Montgomery is the Jumpstart Inclusive Playground, a 15000 square feet of play space designed so that children of all abilities can play together in harmony. This hidden gem is yet another aspect that makes Montgomery the warm and family-friendly community that it is.</p>
                <p>Montgomery is also an excellent neighbourhood for canine lovers with numerous veterinary services, dog parks, spas and daycare facilities. Montgomery is well connected with excellent neighbours: Market Mall on the North West, the new Alberta Children's Hospital on the East and the soon-to-be-developed University of Calgary's West Campus.</p>
                <p>The community is well served with schools for all grades, including Terrace Road Elementary School (Public) and the "Foundations for the Future" charter academy, which serves grades 9-12. The active community association of Montgomery regularly holds events, including annual events that provide fun and entertainment for kids and adults alike. A favourite community event is 'Light Up Montgomery', an annual holiday event that takes place during the last weekend of November with fire pits, hot chocolate, apple cider and Instagram-worthy light installations. Other programs and events held by the community association include a self-guided historical walking tour and the annual 'Humpty's Awards.'</p>
                <p>Eating out in Montgomery is characterized by diverse offerings with Aksa Wiener Schnitzel Haus, Five Spice Kitchen, Papa Nikolas Pizza and Abbey's Creations, some of the must-visit restaurants in the neighbourhood. If you are looking for a fancier meal in the suburbs with downtown energy, the award-winning open kitchen restaurant NOtable is a great option with an excellent vegetarian and vegan-friendly menu.</p>
            </div>
