        <div style="margin-top: 3rem;">
            <h3>Montgomery, Calgary Homes</h3>
            <p>Montgomery is a residential neighbourhood in North West Calgary, bisecting the Tran-Canada Highway. Established in 1911, Montgomery was an autonomous village until being amalgamated by the City of Calgary in 1963, along with Bowness. Situated in a bow shaped portion of the Bow River, Montgomery is a community with a small town atmosphere, with fresh air and green vegetation.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top: 3rem;">
            <h3>Montgomery Real Estate Listings</h3>
            <p>Community Established 1911 <br>Similiar neighbouring community of <a href="https://www.real-estate.ca/bowness.php" target="_self">Bowness</a>.<br><br>Several of the homes in Calgary's Montgomery are located on the south slope of the River Valley escarpment. These homes enjoy nice Bow River Valley views and are also very close to the Shouldice Athletic Park and the Bowmont Natural Environment Park, with its web of bike trails and natural greenery. The lands varied topography is formed primarily from a variety of slopes and landforms. A wide range of different housing developments has formed as a result. </p>
            <p>As of 2006, Montgomery was mostly made up of residential attached and detached single-family homes (bungalow, two storey), which makes up 71.8% of the market, with the remaining 28.2% being apartments and condominiums. 37.9% of homes were being used for rental purposes.</p>
        </div>
