            <div class="x6 last">
                <div>
                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Shopping &mdash;</h3>
                    <p>Montgomery has a small but vibrant shopping community with just over 115 local businesses, including spa, salon and pet care services, thrift stores, florists and automotive repair shops. The neighbourhood also has easily accessible grocery stores and convenience shops such as Safeway, Mary's Corner Store, Save on Foods and Sexsmith Grocery. In addition, Montgomery's Farmers Market connects residents to local food producers and opens every Saturday from May through October. Just North of Montgomery, residents have access to Market Mall, one of the biggest malls in the city of Calgary. The underdevelopment Bow River Shopping Center located in the nearby neighbourhood of Bowness will provide another excellent shopping destination for Montgomery once completed. </p>
                </div>
                <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Parks &mdash;</h3>
                    <p>Shouldice Park is one of the most prominent parks in Montgomery and offers 28 hectares of active space with picnic sites, batting cages and access to Bow River. The park also houses a massive athletic park with fields for playing soccer, football, softball and baseball.</p>
                    <p>The Shouldice Aquatic Center and Shouldice Arena are other areas of interest within the park. Another beautiful park located close to Montgomery is Edworthy Park which offers beautiful hiking trails, biking and walking paths, a riverfront and play structures.</p>
                    <p>For residents in need of a quiet lounge, the hilltop benches in Monyalban Park and Home Road Park provide beautiful vistas of the valley and Bow River. Montgomery also sits just at the beginning of Bowmont Natural Environment Park, which, coupled with being part of the Bow River Pathway System, makes Montgomery ideal for outdoor lovers. The 192-hectare urban park, Bowmont, includes grasslands, gullies, valleys, a waterfall with a lookout, hiking, walking, cycling trails and access to the river for swimming and fishing.</p>
                    <p>Montgomery is home to the Jumpstart Inclusive Playground Project, an accessible playground space of 15,000 square feet for children of all abilities to play together. Dog owners can take advantage of the dedicated off-leash dog park: Shouldice Off-Leash Dog Park. For mountain bikers who want to practice safely, the Montgomery Bike Park provides an excellent option.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div><!-- Montgomery  Amenities -->

    <div style="margin-top: 80px;">
        <h2>General feel and vibe &mdash; What's it like living in Montgomery ?</h2>
        <div>
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Avenue Magazine Rankings</h3>
            <p>Montgomery ranked 21st on Avenue Magazine's 2020 rankings of best neighbourhoods.</p>
        </div>
    </div><!-- Montgomery  Feel and Vibe -->

    <div style="margin-top: 80px;">
        <h2>Interesting Facts about Montgomery </h2>
        <div>
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Schools In or Near Montgomery </h3>
            <p>Families looking to make Montgomery home will be pleased to note that there are public, French and separate elementary, junior high and high schools in the neighbourhood. Terrace Road Elementary is a public school located in Montgomery and Foundations for the Future Charter School takes place at the Montgomery Junior High School. Bowness High School serves Grades 10-12 in Montgomery.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Demographics</h3>
            <p>The small community of Montgomery has a population of 4,873 residents, with 56% being married couples and 33% being families with kids. The median age of residents is 37.8. The median household income before taxes in Montgomery is $77, 561. </p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Housing</h3>
            <p>The warm inner-city community of Montgomery in North West Calgary offers plenty of affordable housing options. The community is on the upswing and will get an extra boost once the University district is developed. Homebuyers have plenty of options to choose from-starting with single-family homes to condominium units and even townhomes. As a neighbourhood with a long history, some homes in Montgomery are older. But there are plenty of modern constructions for people looking for more 21st century designs.</p>
            <p>Many older homes in Montgomery have been revamped with tasteful modern designs, well-kept yards and majestic maple trees. The newer homes in Montgomery, on the other hand, combine luxuries like massive master bedrooms, in-suite spa bathrooms, open floor plans and expansive kitchen space. The best homes in Montgomery are located next to the community green spaces and present stunning views of the Bow River.</p>
        </div>
    </div><!-- Montgomery  Facts -->

